Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.40,0:02:40.17,Default,,0,0,0,,很久以前 只靠火光照亮\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A long time ago, in a world lit only by fire,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.20,0:02:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,我們和繁星之間的關係\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}our relationship with the stars
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.03,0:02:44.27,Default,,0,0,0,,非常的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}was far more...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.30,0:02:45.77,Default,,0,0,0,,貼心\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}personal.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.81,0:02:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,幾千代人以來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}For thousands of generations,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.51,0:02:50.74,Default,,0,0,0,,我們將繁星視作生活不可或缺的部分\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}we watched the stars as if our lives depended on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.74,0:02:53.14,Default,,0,0,0,,確實如此\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Because they did.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.67,0:02:57.55,Default,,0,0,0,,我們人類不算最大\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We humans were not the biggest, the strongest,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.71,0:03:00.43,Default,,0,0,0,,也不是最強壯或者最快的相比其他動物而言\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14} nor the fastest of all the animals we competed against.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.59,0:03:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,但我們有個特長\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But we did have one thing going for us...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.59,0:03:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的智慧\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}our intelligence.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.36,0:03:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,其中一點就是識別圖形的天賦\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}One aspect of that was a genius for pattern recognition
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.19,0:03:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,夜復一夜 我們仰望星空\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Night after night, we watched the stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.90,0:03:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的祖先慢慢地注意到\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And over time, our ancestors noticed
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.87,0:03:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,夜空中星星的移動預示著地球上的變化\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that the motions of the stars across the nights of the year foretold changes on Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.87,0:03:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,威脅或者增加我們生存的機會\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that threatened or enhanced our chances for survival.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.74,0:03:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,在我們只能依靠想像力來體會故事的年代\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In a time when our imaginations were the only stage where stories came to life,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.61,0:03:28.35,Default,,0,0,0,,那時沒有電影或者電視\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}before there were movies or TVs
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.38,0:03:30.85,Default,,0,0,0,,也沒有其他的電子設備\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}or electronic devices of any kind,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.88,0:03:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,不同的文明將這些點連成各自不同的圖案\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}every human culture connected the dots to form their own pictures.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.72,0:03:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,這些圖案變成故事書中的插圖\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}These images became the illustrations of a storybook
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.63,0:03:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,更深層面說來 也是一本生存手冊\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that, on a deeper level, was also a survival manual.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.46,0:03:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,天神和英雄們的名字個性\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The names and personalities of the gods, heroes,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.57,0:03:49.70,Default,,0,0,0,,還有動物或者類似物體的名字和個性\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}farm animals or familiar objects
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.74,0:03:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,在各個文化中各不相同\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}varied from culture to culture.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.94,0:03:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,除了一組特定的美麗星團\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But there was one particularly gorgeous group of stars
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.38,0:04:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,從古希臘人到現在的我們都叫它\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}known to the Ancient Greeks and to us today
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.11,0:04:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,昴宿星團\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}as the Pleiades,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.11,0:04:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fn方正黑体简体\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}其位於金牛座 裸眼就可以輕易的看見 肉眼通常見到有六顆亮星
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.45,0:04:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,大約1億年前形成的星團\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a star cluster formed about 100 million years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.95,0:04:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,每顆星都比太陽明亮40倍左右\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Each of them is some 40 times brighter than our Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.29,0:04:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,昴宿六是最亮的一顆\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And Alcyone, the most luminous,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.29,0:04:15.79,Default,,0,0,0,,比太陽亮1000倍\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}outshines our Sun 1,000 times.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.83,0:04:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,以前昂宿星團被用來檢測視力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}For ages, the Pleiades have been used as an eye test
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.80,0:04:22.10,Default,,0,0,0,,而且世界通用\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for people all over the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.13,0:04:24.97,Default,,0,0,0,,能看到6顆\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If you could see at least six of them,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.00,0:04:26.81,Default,,0,0,0,,就是普通人的標準\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}you were considered normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.84,0:04:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,看到超過7顆\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If you saw more than seven,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.67,0:04:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,就符合戰士或者偵察兵的標準了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}you were an ideal candidate for a warrior or scout.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.81,0:04:34.95,Default,,0,0,0,,對於古凱爾特人和不列顛群島的德魯伊特來說\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Among the Ancient Celts and Druids of the British Isles,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.98,0:04:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,他們相信昂宿星團和亡魂有關\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the Pleiades were believed to have a haunting significance.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.35,0:04:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,一年中它們升到天空最高點的那一晚的午夜\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}On the night of the year that they reach the highest point in the sky at midnight,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.42,0:04:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,亡魂會在地球上遊蕩\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the spirits of the dead were thought to wander the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.09,0:04:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,據信這是一個節日的起源\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This is believed to be the origin of the holiday
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.00,0:04:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,以前叫薩溫節\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}once known as Samhain,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.10,0:04:52.60,Default,,0,0,0,,現在叫萬聖節\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}now called Halloween.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.63,0:04:54.93,Default,,0,0,0,,在世界各地 我們的祖先用\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}All over the Earth, our ancestors told
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.97,0:04:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,各種神奇的故事\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}wonderful stories to explain
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.04,0:05:00.41,Default,,0,0,0,,來解釋昂宿星團的來歷\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}how the Pleiades came to be in the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.44,0:05:02.77,Default,,0,0,0,,以北美洲的基奧瓦人來說\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}For the Kiowa people of North America,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.81,0:05:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,故事是這樣的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}it happened something like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.65,0:05:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,很久很久以前 一些小姑娘\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Long, long ago, some young women
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.45,0:05:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,溜出他們的營地\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}snuck away from their campsite
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.56,0:05:19.99,Default,,0,0,0,,在星空下無拘無束的跳舞\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to dance freely beneath the stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.69,0:05:55.39,Default,,0,0,0,,山神 救命啊\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Rock, save us!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.43,0:05:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,山神 可憐可憐我們吧\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Rock, take pity on us!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.03,0:06:03.07,Default,,0,0,0,,山神聽到了她們的哭聲 升起了一座高高的山峰\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The rock heard their cries and grew taller.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.91,0:06:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,變成了今天的魔鬼峰\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Until it became what is today known as the Devil's Tower.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.72,0:06:21.99,Default,,0,0,0,,這些姑娘變成了昂宿星團的星星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The maidens were transformed into the stars of the Pleiades,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.02,0:06:25.62,Default,,0,0,0,,冬至的時候可以看到她們高高的掛在山峰上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}which may be seen hanging above the tower in midwinter.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.53,0:06:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,古希臘人也將這7顆明珠\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The Ancient Greeks also saw those seven jewels
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.86,0:06:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,看做7位少女\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}as seven maidens,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.96,0:06:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,阿特拉斯的7個女兒\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the seven daughters of Atlas,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.96,0:06:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fn方正黑体简体\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}負責以肩頂天的神
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.57,0:06:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fn方正黑体简体\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}指的是獵戶座的那個獵戶
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.57,0:06:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,不是被熊追 而是被俄裏翁追\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}pursued not by bears, but by...Orion the hunter
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.31,0:06:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,他出來溜達的時候看到了她們\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}who spied them when he was out walking one day.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.29,0:06:55.89,Default,,0,0,0,,俄裏翁這個獵戶獸性大發\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Orion became mad with desire.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.90,0:07:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,追了她們7年 直到有一天\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}For seven years, he chased them relentlessly.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.23,0:07:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,終於精疲力盡了 -宙斯 救命啊\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}- Exhausted... - Zeus, help us.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.60,0:07:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,她們向宙斯呼救\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}...they prayed to Zeus for deliverance.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.24,0:07:19.71,Default,,0,0,0,,眾神之王宙斯大發慈悲\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Zeus, the king of the gods, felt sorry for them,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.75,0:07:21.95,Default,,0,0,0,,把她們7個\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and transformed those seven maidens
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.98,0:07:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,變成了昂宿星團\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}into the Pleiades.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.79,0:07:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,但是 神就是神經病\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But the gods are, if anything, capricious.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.16,0:07:39.73,Default,,0,0,0,,俄裏翁被蝎子蟄死後\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When Orion was killed by the sting of a scorpion,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.77,0:07:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,宙斯把他放在上天 讓他可以繼續追逐這7位姐妹\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Zeus placed him in the sky where he could resume his pursuit of the seven gorgeous sisters
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.10,0:07:48.81,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的祖先編織了各種美麗的傳說\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Our ancestors, they wove brilliantly imaginative stories
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.84,0:07:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,但是除了想像 並不能讓我們更接近這些星星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But they can bring us no closer to the stars than our dreams
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.68,0:07:55.45,Default,,0,0,0,,直到很多年後\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It took yet another few thousand years
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.48,0:08:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,才有3位聰明的科學家揭開了這些星星的神秘面紗\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}until three brilliant scientists unlocked the secrets of the true lives of the stars
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.74,0:08:15.37,Default,,0,0,0,,1901年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In 1901,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.41,0:08:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,哈佛是男人的天下\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Harvard was a man's world.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.38,0:08:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,直到一位名叫愛德華·查爾斯·皮克林的天文學家\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But an astronomer named Edward Charles Pickering
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.14,0:08:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,打破了這個規矩\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}broke that rule.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.72,0:08:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,噢 皮克林的辦公室就在走廊盡頭\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Oh, Pickering's office is just down the hallway.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.69,0:08:30.85,Default,,0,0,0,,那扇門的後面\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And that door over there leads to the room
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.89,0:08:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,就是他的機房\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}where he keeps his computers.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.10,0:08:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,說起來 這些女人都是「計算機」 但是\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We're supposed to call those women "computers," but, uh,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.84,0:08:51.41,Default,,0,0,0,,我聽到不少人叫她們\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I've heard more than one fellow refer to those gals
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.44,0:08:54.34,Default,,0,0,0,,皮克林的後宮\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}as "Pickering's Harem."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.38,0:08:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,皮克林招募了一群婦女\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Pickering assembled a team of women
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.75,0:08:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,給星星分類 繪製星圖\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to map and classify the types of stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.75,0:09:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,其中一位為我們瞭解恆星的物質提供了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}One of them provided the key to our understanding
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.22,0:09:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,關鍵的鑰匙\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of the substance of the stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.92,0:09:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,還有一位給我們提供了計算\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And another devised a way for us to calculate
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.76,0:09:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,宇宙體積的方法\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the size of the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.73,0:09:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,你可能從沒聽說過她們\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}For some reason, you probably never heard of either of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.40,0:09:16.87,Default,,0,0,0,,想知道原因嗎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Wonder why.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.54,0:09:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,這個小組的組長名叫安妮·坎農\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That's Annie Jump Cannon, the leader of the team.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.24,0:09:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,完成時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Before she was through,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.14,0:09:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,她分類了25萬顆恆星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}she catalogued a quarter of a million stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.25,0:09:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,11號是一顆B7星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Number 11 is a B7.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.75,0:09:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,那是昂宿星團的昂宿六\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That's Alcyone in the Pleiades.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.72,0:09:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,在坎農還年輕的時候\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Cannon lost her hearing during a bout of scarlet fever
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.25,0:09:38.45,Default,,0,0,0,,她不幸因為感染猩紅熱而喪失了聽力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}when she was a young woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.49,0:09:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,12號是一顆B6星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Number 12 is a B6.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.93,0:09:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,那是亨麗愛塔·勒維特 也是失聰\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That's Henrietta Swan Leavitt. She's also deaf.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.80,0:09:48.73,Default,,0,0,0,,她是這裏的另一位偉大的科學家\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And she's the other great scientist in the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.77,0:09:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,勒維特發明了天文學家沿用上百年的方法\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Leavitt discovered the law that astronomers still use more than a century later
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.74,0:09:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,用來測量恆星之間的距離\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to measure the distances to the stars
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.61,0:09:58.17,Default,,0,0,0,,還有宇宙的體積\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and the size of the cosmos itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.14,0:10:03.05,Default,,0,0,0,,安妮·坎農在一張賀卡中說明了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Annie Jump Cannon sent out a Christmas card explaining
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.08,0:10:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,她們正在從事的工作\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}what she and her sisters were actually doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.15,0:10:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,恆星發出的光可以\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The light from a star is allowed
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.12,0:10:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,通過望遠鏡中的棱鏡 她寫道\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to fall through a prism placed in the telescope, she wrote.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.62,0:10:15.29,Default,,0,0,0,,經過放大 星光可以分解成一組色帶\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Thus magnified, the starlight is split up into a band
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.33,0:10:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,顯示出組成的顏色\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}showing its component colors,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.76,0:10:22.06,Default,,0,0,0,,紅光和紫光分別處於兩端\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the red rays going to one end and the violet to the other.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.10,0:10:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是恆星的光譜\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This is the spectrum of the star.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.47,0:10:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,由深色細線表示\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It shows the presence of fine, dark lines.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.37,0:10:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,將這些細線與實驗室中發光物質做對比\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}By comparing them with lines given by glowing substances in the laboratory
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.84,0:10:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,我們可以斷定這些地球上熟悉的物質\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}we can determine that the same elements familiar to us
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.48,0:10:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,同樣存在於遙遠的恆星上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}on the Earth also exist in the outermost star.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.79,0:10:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,這是12358B號\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This is plate number 12358B.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.84,0:11:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,這塊板上的第一號是顆B類星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Number one at this plate is a B-type star.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.58,0:11:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,定為B2\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Make that a B2.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.35,0:11:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,坎農用了幾十年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It took Cannon decades
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.08,0:11:14.95,Default,,0,0,0,,按照光譜特性\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to classify the spectral character
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.99,0:11:17.39,Default,,0,0,0,,為成千上萬的恆星分門別類\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of hundreds of thousands of stars
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.42,0:11:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,根據她制定的方法\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}according to the scheme that she devised.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.99,0:11:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,坎農認為恆星可以\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Cannon discovered that the stars fell
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.43,0:11:28.83,Default,,0,0,0,,根據它們的光譜線圖被分為7大類\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}into a continuous sequence of seven broad categories according to their spectral line patterns.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.87,0:11:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,每個大類由一個字母代表\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Each was designated by a letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.24,0:11:35.14,Default,,0,0,0,,但是相同類別的兩顆恆星的光譜線\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But the spectral lines of two stars in the same letter class
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.17,0:11:37.31,Default,,0,0,0,,可能有著細微的區別\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}could differ in subtle ways,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.34,0:11:41.21,Default,,0,0,0,,坎農根據記憶察覺到的細微變化\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}minute variations that Cannon learned to recognize from memory.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.25,0:11:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,為了區分這些光譜\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}To distinguish these spectra from one another,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.91,0:11:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,她又將每大類分為10個用數字代表的小類\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}she assigned ten numerical subcategories for each class.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.59,0:11:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,安妮·坎農將恆星歸類\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Annie Jump Cannon organized the stars,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.42,0:11:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,另一位科學家負責解密她的成果中隱藏的含義\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but it would fall to another scientist to decipher the hidden meaning in her work
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.06,0:12:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,1923年的英格蘭 婦女無權\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In the England of 1923, women were forbidden
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.53,0:12:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,在科學上獲得高級學位\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}from pursuing advanced degrees in science.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.90,0:12:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,但是塞西莉亞·佩恩在倫敦參加了一個講座\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But Cecelia Payne had attended a lecture in London
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.80,0:12:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,由亞瑟·愛丁頓爵士演講\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}by the astronomer Sir Arthur Eddington,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.07,0:12:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,他是首位證實\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the first scientist to provide evidence
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.71,0:12:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,愛因斯坦廣義相對論的科學家\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that Einstein's revolutionary General Theory of Relativity was correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.58,0:12:17.08,Default,,0,0,0,,從那時起\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}From that moment on,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.11,0:12:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,她知道沒什麼可以阻擋她\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}she knew that nothing would deter her
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.82,0:12:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,追求她的夢想\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}from pursing her big dreams.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.79,0:12:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,她決定移居美國\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}She resolved to emigrate to America,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.16,0:12:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,在那裏婦女已經有了研究恆星的自由\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}where women had already gained the freedom to study the stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.63,0:12:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,哈佛大學接受了她的申請\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Her application was accepted at Harvard.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.66,0:12:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,她隨後的發現改變了一個天文學的基本觀點\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What she would discover there would challenge one of the central beliefs of astronomy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.30,0:12:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,造成的影響就如同現代天文物理學的曙光\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The resulting impact would be the dawn of modern astrophysics.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.64,0:12:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,幾十年過去了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}As the decades passed,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.48,0:12:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,安妮·坎農和她的組員不斷地篩分恆星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Annie Jump Cannon and her team kept sifting the stars,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.71,0:12:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,檢查每一顆的光譜特徵\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}checking each one's spectral signature
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.55,0:13:02.35,Default,,0,0,0,,並將它們歸入\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}with a fleeting glance and then dropping them
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.39,0:13:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,7大分類中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}into one of seven categories.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.22,0:13:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,它們變成了圖片中成千上萬的像素\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They became hundreds of thousands of dots
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.06,0:13:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,在當時還沒人能夠瞭解它的含義\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in a larger picture which no one could yet understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.39,0:13:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,這支隊伍中又來了一位新的成員\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Into this community of women came one more.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.67,0:13:18.37,Default,,0,0,0,,哈嘍\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Well, hello there.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.40,0:13:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,你就是佩恩吧\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}You must be Miss Payne.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.57,0:13:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,等你好久啦\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We've been waiting for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.87,0:13:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,快進來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Come on in.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.08,0:13:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,塞西莉亞·佩恩第一次在科研環境中受到這樣的歡迎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Cecilia Payne had never experienced such kindness in a scientific setting before.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.35,0:13:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,姐妹們無私的與她分享研究成果\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This sisterhood generously shared the fruits of their labors with her,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.12,0:13:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,她將她們的觀察結果\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and she turned their observations
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.95,0:13:40.49,Default,,0,0,0,,轉化成一種對恆星的全新認識\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}into a radical new understanding of the stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.52,0:13:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,兩個女人變成了非常要好的朋友\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The two women became great friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.66,0:13:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,坎農把恆星光譜對佩恩傾囊相授\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Cannon taught Payne everything she had learned about stellar spectra
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.93,0:13:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,佩恩著手分析坎農的數據\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And Payne began to analyze Cannon's data
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.73,0:13:54.67,Default,,0,0,0,,嘗試著判斷恆星中的化學成分與物理狀態\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to see if she could determine the actual chemical composition and physical state of the stars
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.71,0:13:58.87,Default,,0,0,0,,她發揮了她的理論原子物理學專長\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}She brought to this work her expertise in theoretical and atomic physics
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.71,0:14:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,恆星光譜中最突出的特徵\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The most prominent features in the spectra of stars
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.58,0:14:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,顯示了重金屬元素的存在 比如鈣 和鐵\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}showed the presence of heavy elements such as calcium... and iron,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.29,0:14:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,地球上最常見的那些元素\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}which are among the most abundant elements in the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.26,0:14:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,天文學家自然而然的得出結論\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}So astronomers naturally concluded
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.26,0:14:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,恆星是由與地球相同的物質組成\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that the stars were made of the same elements as the Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.10,0:14:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,就連比例都大致相同\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and in roughly the same proportions.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.26,0:14:26.14,Default,,0,0,0,,1924年 當時的美國天文學泰斗亨利·諾利斯·羅素\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In 1924, Henry Norris Russell was the dean
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.17,0:14:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,為我們對於恆星的瞭解做出了重大的貢獻\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of American astronomers having made major contributions to our understanding of the stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.84,0:14:36.45,Default,,0,0,0,,地球上的40到45號化學元素\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}40 to 45 of the chemical elements that we have here on Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.48,0:14:39.25,Default,,0,0,0,,一樣存在與太陽的光譜中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}are also present in the spectrum of the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.28,0:14:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,所以我們可以推斷太陽的成分\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}So we can assume that the composition of the Sun
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.82,0:14:45.66,Default,,0,0,0,,與地球類似\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}resembles that of the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.69,0:14:49.16,Default,,0,0,0,,如果有人能把地殼加熱到發出光芒\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If one were to heat the crust of the Earth to incandescence,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.19,0:14:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,它的光譜就會和太陽類似\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}its spectrum would resemble that of the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.34,0:15:13.18,Default,,0,0,0,,安妮 我明白了這麼多年來你的工作成果的真正意義\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Annie, I think I now understand what it all means. All your years of work.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.22,0:15:14.45,Default,,0,0,0,,說來聽聽\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.48,0:15:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,我計算了不同溫度下的光譜\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I've calculated what the spectra should look like across a wide range of temperatures,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.19,0:15:22.66,Default,,0,0,0,,它們和你的分類法完美吻合\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and they match your system of classification perfectly
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.69,0:15:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,恆星的光譜可以表示它的溫度\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The spectrum of any star tells you exactly how hot it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.90,0:15:32.87,Default,,0,0,0,,你的OBAFGKM就是恆星的溫標\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Your "O-B-A-F-G-K-M" is really a temperature scale of the stars
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.90,0:15:32.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fn方正黑体简体\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}OBAFGKM=哈佛分類法 各個字母代表不同的光譜類別
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.90,0:15:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,從最熱到最冷\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}from the hottest to the coldest.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.57,0:15:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,重點來了 安妮 多虧了你\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Here's the headline, Annie. Thanks to your work,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.41,0:15:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,我發現 恆星幾乎全部是由氫和氦組成\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I've discovered that the stars are made almost entirely of hydrogen and helium.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.15,0:15:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,恆星中的氫和氦比金屬多上百萬倍\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There's a million times more hydrogen and helium than the metals in the stars
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.42,0:15:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道聽上去好像挺傻\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I know, it sounds daft.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.09,0:15:54.12,Default,,0,0,0,,你確定嗎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Are you certain?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.16,0:15:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,有人核對過你的計算結果嗎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Has anyone else checked your calculations?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.90,0:16:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,還沒 我都寫進我的論文裏了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Not yet, but it's all in my thesis,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.50,0:16:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,已經寄給羅素教授了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}which is already on its way to Professor Russell.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.55,0:16:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,倒霉孩子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Poor woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.61,0:16:20.85,Default,,0,0,0,,羅素對她表示遺憾\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Russell felt sorry for Cecilia Payne.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.88,0:16:24.39,Default,,0,0,0,,在他看來 她的論文從根本上就是錯的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Her thesis appeared to him to be fundamentally flawed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.96,0:16:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,顯然氫和氦不可能比金屬多上百萬倍\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It is clearly impossible that hydrogen should be a million times more abundant than the metals.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.31,0:16:48.74,Default,,0,0,0,,她仔細收集的證據與傳統的科學觀點不相符\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Her carefully gathered evidence flew in the face of conventional scientific wisdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.78,0:16:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,我怎麼可能是對的 她問\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}"How could I be right," she asked,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.75,0:16:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,那就意味著\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}"if that must mean
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.98,0:16:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,那麼著名的科學家錯了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that such a distinguished scientist was wrong?"
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.65,0:17:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,儘管她對自己的研究結果很自信\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Despite her confidence in the quality of her research,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.72,0:17:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,她還是在她的論文裏加上了一句 「高的幾乎可以肯定不真實」\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}she caved and added a sentence to her thesis
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.83,0:17:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,動搖了這個非常偉大的觀點\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that undermined its greatest insight.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.34,0:17:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,4年後\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It would be four years
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.80,0:17:16.54,Default,,0,0,0,,羅素才意識到佩恩是正確的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}before Russell realized that Payne was right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.57,0:17:19.71,Default,,0,0,0,,值得表揚的是 他一認識到這點\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}To his credit, as soon as he did,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.74,0:17:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,他就承認了 這是佩恩的發現\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}he acknowledged that it was her discovery.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.52,0:17:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,佩恩的《恆星大氣》被普遍看做是\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Payne's "Stellar Atmospheres" is widely regarded
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.35,0:17:33.29,Default,,0,0,0,,天文學有史以來最傑出的博士論文\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}as the most brilliant PhD thesis ever written in astronomy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.32,0:17:37.66,Default,,0,0,0,,它成了這個領域裏教科書\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It became the standard text in its field.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.69,0:17:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,沒有堅持我的觀點是我的責任\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I was to blame for not having pressed my point.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.43,0:17:46.27,Default,,0,0,0,,儘管我相信自己的正確 卻還是屈服於權威\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I had given in to authority when I believed I was right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.30,0:17:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你對自己的結論有把握\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If you are sure of your facts,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.37,0:17:50.81,Default,,0,0,0,,你就應該堅持你的立場\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}you should defend your position.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.37,0:17:50.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fn方正黑体简体\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}恆星大氣學
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.21,0:17:56.99,Default,,0,0,0,,在其他領域 權威的言論可能佔優勢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The words of the powerful may prevail in other spheres of human experience
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.31,0:17:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.15,0:18:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,但對科學來說 最關鍵的是證據\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but in science, the only thing that counts is the evidence
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.15,0:18:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,以及爭議本身的邏輯性\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and the logic of the argument itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.65,0:18:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,佩恩解釋了安妮坎農的恆星光譜序列\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Cecilia Payne's interpretation of Annie Jump Cannon's sequence
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.06,0:18:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,使我們可以理解恆星生命的故事\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of stellar spectra made it possible for us to read the life stories of the stars
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.06,0:18:19.07,Default,,0,0,0,,並且根據這個從它燃燒的終點追溯回它的起源\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and to trace the story of life itself back to its beginnings in their fiery deaths.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.44,0:18:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,有很多種恆星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There are many kinds of stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.25,0:18:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,一些像太陽般明亮\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Some are bright like the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.82,0:18:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,有些暗淡\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Some are dim.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.95,0:18:40.29,Default,,0,0,0,,最大的恆星比最小的要大上千萬倍\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The greatest stars are ten million\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}times larger than the smallest ones
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.32,0:18:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,有些恆星古老的超出想像\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Some stars are old beyond imagining,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.93,0:18:46.09,Default,,0,0,0,,超過100億歲\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}more than ten billion years of age.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.13,0:18:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,有些才剛剛誕生\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Others are being born right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.20,0:18:55.17,Default,,0,0,0,,當原子在恆星的核心中融合\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When atoms fuse in the hearts of stars,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.20,0:18:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,它們發出星光\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}they make starlight.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.51,0:18:58.41,Default,,0,0,0,,恆星從雜物中誕生\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Stars are born in litters,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.44,0:19:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,由星際雲的氣體和灰塵組成\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}formed from the gas and dust of interstellar clouds.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.11,0:19:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,不同恆星的質量差異\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The mass of the individual stars in a litter
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.05,0:19:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,從小的那些 並不比最大的行星大多少\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}can range from the runts--not much larger than the largest planets--
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.45,0:19:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,到大的那些超巨星 讓太陽都相形見絀\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to the supergiant stars that dwarf the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.39,0:19:22.30,Default,,0,0,0,,獵戶座腰帶下方星雲中的恆星剛剛誕生\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The stars in the nebula below Orion's Belt are newborns,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.33,0:19:24.03,Default,,0,0,0,,差不多500萬歲\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}around five million years old,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.07,0:19:29.47,Default,,0,0,0,,還被包裹在誕生時的氣體和灰塵中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and still swaddled in the gas and dust that gave birth to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.51,0:19:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,昂宿星團中的恆星已經到了蹣跚學步的年紀\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The stars in the Pleiades are already toddlers,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.68,0:19:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,1億歲左右\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}about 100 million years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.58,0:19:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,它們已經甩開了氣體和灰塵的遮蓋\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They've shed their blankets of gas and dust,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.71,0:19:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,但依然被彼此的引力束縛在一起\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but they're still bound together by their mutual gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.58,0:19:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,再過幾億年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Another few hundred million years,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.52,0:19:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,它們才會各奔東西\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and they'll drift apart and go their separate ways,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.15,0:19:47.66,Default,,0,0,0,,從此再不相見\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}never to meet again.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.69,0:19:51.29,Default,,0,0,0,,北斗星中的大部分恆星已經是青少年了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Most of the stars of the Big Dipper are adolescents,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.33,0:19:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,5億歲左右\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}roughly half a billion years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.90,0:19:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,它們已經離開了出生時的星團\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They've already drifted apart from their birth cluster,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.50,0:19:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,不過 我們還是能找到它們共同的祖先\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}although we can still trace their common ancestry.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.57,0:20:02.97,Default,,0,0,0,,最終 它們會散落在銀河系中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Eventually, they'll spread out around the Milky Way galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.01,0:20:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,但是大部分常見的星座\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But most of the familiar constellations
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.88,0:20:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,是由完全不相關的恆星混合而成\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}are a mix of entirely unrelated stars,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.25,0:20:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,有些暗淡而相距不遠\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}some faint and nearby,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.05,0:20:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,有些明亮遠遠相隔\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}others bright and far away.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.72,0:20:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的太陽呢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Our own Sun?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.29,0:20:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,從幾光年開外看去 也很難找到其他相近的恆星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}From the distance of even a few light-years, it's hard to find amidst the other stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.73,0:20:25.73,Default,,0,0,0,,那個\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.36,0:20:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的太陽已進中年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Our Sun is middle-aged
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.90,0:20:30.83,Default,,0,0,0,,離開出生地也很遠了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and a long way from where it was born.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.87,0:20:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,從同一個星際雲誕生的姐妹星們\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Its sister stars hatched from the same interstellar cloud,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.37,0:20:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,分散在銀河系各處\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}are dispersed throughout the galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.24,0:20:39.87,Default,,0,0,0,,許多都有它們各自的行星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Many of them have their own planets.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.91,0:20:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,或許有些已經孕育了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Perhaps some of them nurture
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.81,0:20:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,智慧生物和生命的進化\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the evolution of life and intelligence.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.91,0:20:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,夜空中的大多數恆星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Most of the stars in our night sky
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.05,0:20:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,會環繞一個或多個恆星小夥伴運行\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}actually orbit around one or more stellar companions.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.72,0:20:53.79,Default,,0,0,0,,在這種雙星或者多星的系統內 靠我們的肉眼\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}With the naked eye, we usually can't see the fainter members
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.82,0:20:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,通常看不到較暗的那些星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in such double and multiple star systems.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.79,0:21:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,在有3個太陽的世界裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}On a world with three suns,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.73,0:21:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,很少有夜晚\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the nights would be rare
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.67,0:21:06.30,Default,,0,0,0,,白天也在紅色和藍色中交替\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and the days might alternate between red and blue.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.81,0:21:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,恆星的坍縮是注定的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It is the destiny of stars to collapse.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.58,0:21:19.71,Default,,0,0,0,,抬頭看向夜空 所看到的成千上萬的星星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Of the thousands of stars you see when you look up at the night sky,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.75,0:21:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,每一個都活在兩次坍縮之間\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}every one of them is living in an interval between two collapses...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.25,0:21:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,黑暗的星際氣體雲團的第一次坍縮\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}an initial collapse of a dark, interstellar gas cloud
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.12,0:21:27.72,Default,,0,0,0,,形成了恆星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to form the star,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.76,0:21:30.29,Default,,0,0,0,,明亮恆星的最後一次坍縮\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and a final collapse of the luminous star
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.33,0:21:33.06,Default,,0,0,0,,是它的生命盡頭\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}on its way to its ultimate fate.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.10,0:21:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,沒有外力干擾的情況下 引力使恆星收縮\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Gravity makes stars contract, unless some other force intervenes
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.03,0:21:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,太陽是個熾熱氣體組成的大球體\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The Sun is a great, big ball of incandescent gas.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.37,0:21:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,核心的超高溫氣體\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The super hot gas in its core
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.34,0:21:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,促使太陽向外擴張\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}pushes the Sun to expand outward.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.37,0:21:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,與此同時 太陽的引力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}At the same time,the Sun's own gravity
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.21,0:21:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,又使它向內收縮\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}pulls it inward to contract.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.28,0:21:54.85,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的太陽處在兩種力穩定平衡的狀態\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And our Sun is poised between these two forces in a stable equilibrium
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.88,0:21:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,引力和核爆炸\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}between gravity and nuclear fire,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.05,0:21:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,這種平衡會繼續\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a balance it will maintain
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.56,0:22:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,保持40億年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for another four billion years.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.89,0:22:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,太陽消耗氫氣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But as the Sun consumes hydrogen,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.23,0:22:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,它的核心慢慢的收縮\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}its core very slowly shrinks,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.20,0:22:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,而它的表面卻在逐步的擴張\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and the Sun's surface gradually expands in response.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.70,0:22:15.37,Default,,0,0,0,,在幾百萬年的時間裏 過程很緩慢 不易察覺\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It happens very slowly,imperceptibly, over the course of millions of years
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.40,0:22:17.47,Default,,0,0,0,,但對於10億年來說\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But in about a billion years,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.51,0:22:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,太陽會比現在亮出百分之10\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the Sun will be ten percent brighter than it is today
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.31,0:22:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,百分之10 聽上去不多\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Ten percent may not sound like much,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.32,0:22:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,但這些額外的熱量會對地球造成很大的影響\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but that extra heat will have a big effect on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.43,0:22:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,當太陽最終耗盡它的核燃料\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When the Sun finally exhausts its nuclear fuel
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.10,0:22:42.73,Default,,0,0,0,,40或者50億年後\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}four or five billion years from now,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.77,0:22:46.37,Default,,0,0,0,,氣體會冷卻 壓力會下降\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}its gas will cool and the pressure will fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.40,0:22:51.01,Default,,0,0,0,,太陽的內部無法繼續支撐外層的重量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The Sun's interior can no longer support the weight of the outer layers
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.04,0:22:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,最初的坍縮再次繼續\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and the initial collapse will resume.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.41,0:22:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,萬物都沒有永恆\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Nothing lasts forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.28,0:22:58.75,Default,,0,0,0,,恆星也會死\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Even the stars die.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.78,0:23:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,氦 100億年來氫聚變的灰燼\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Helium, the ash of ten billion years of hydrogen fusion,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.05,0:23:05.25,Default,,0,0,0,,在核心中匯聚\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}has built up in the core.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.29,0:23:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,沒有核爆炸支持它的重量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}With no nuclear fire to sustain its weight,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.86,0:23:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,內核坍縮 溫度高的開始將氦聚合成碳和氧\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the core collapses until it becomes hot enough to start fusing helium into carbon and oxygen
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.73,0:23:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,太陽內核的溫度比以前高很多\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The core of the Sun is now much hotter than it was before.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.60,0:23:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,它的大氣急劇膨脹\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Its atmosphere rapidly expands.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.37,0:23:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,在接下來的10億年裏 它膨脹到\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Over the next billion years, it'll become bloated
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.47,0:23:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,超過現在體積的100倍\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to more than 100 times its original size
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.98,0:23:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,變成一顆紅巨星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a red giant star.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.08,0:23:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,,它將會覆蓋併吞噬\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It will envelop and devour
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.32,0:23:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,水星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the planets Mercury...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.42,0:23:41.79,Default,,0,0,0,,金星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}...and Venus...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.16,0:23:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,很可能還有地球\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}...and possibly the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.27,0:23:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,我認為\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I like to think that
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.13,0:23:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,在那之前的幾千萬年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}tens of millions of years before that far distant future,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.67,0:23:57.87,Default,,0,0,0,,如果地球上還有生命誕生\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}if there still be life born of Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.91,0:24:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,它們應該已經在其他星球找到了新家\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}it will have found new homes among the stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.48,0:24:05.55,Default,,0,0,0,,一旦太陽燃盡所有的氦\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Once the Sun burns through its helium,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.58,0:24:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,它就開始變得非常不穩定\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}it will become highly unstable,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.78,0:24:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,將它的外圍甩向太空\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}casting off its outer layers into space.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.09,0:24:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,超級炙熱的裸露核心\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The exposed, super hot core
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.86,0:24:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,發出高能量的紫外線 潮水般淹沒四周\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}will flood its surroundings with high-energy ultraviolet light.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.20,0:24:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,原子們發著光 瘋狂的劇烈活動\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The atoms will perform a wild, fluorescent dance.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.21,0:24:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,太陽會像蛋奶酥一樣的收縮塌陷\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The Sun will collapse like a souffle
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.14,0:24:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,縮小到地球體積的幾百倍\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}shrinking a hundredfold to the size of the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.31,0:24:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,到那時 太陽極度緊密 過度擁擠的電子開始相互排擠\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And at that point, the Sun will be so dense that its overcrowded electrons will push back,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.55,0:24:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,一切收縮都停止了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}stopping any further contraction.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.85,0:24:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,只有太陽中心的光核還依然堅持在那裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The kernel of light at the center will be the only part of the Sun that endures
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.06,0:24:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,變成了白矮星 它還會繼續發出微弱的光\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a white dwarf star that will go on shining dimly
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.53,0:24:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,再持續1千億年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for another 100 billion years.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.23,0:24:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,遙遠未來的生命\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Will the beings of a distant future,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.57,0:25:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,從這顆星的殘骸旁路過\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}sailing past this wreck of a star,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.00,0:25:05.87,Default,,0,0,0,,會想到它曾經照耀過得那些生命和世界嗎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}have any idea of the life and worlds that it once warmed?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.15,0:25:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,普通恆星死亡時的炫目光罩轉瞬即逝\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The psychedelic death shrouds of ordinary stars are fleeting,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.29,0:25:37.62,Default,,0,0,0,,只會延續幾萬年的時間\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}lasting only tens of thousands of years
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.66,0:25:41.06,Default,,0,0,0,,然後消散成星際氣體和灰塵\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}before dissipating in the interstellar gas and dust
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.09,0:25:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,新的恆星又會從中誕生\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}from which the new stars will be born.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.63,0:25:50.04,Default,,0,0,0,,聯星系統中的恆星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The stars in a binary star system
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.07,0:25:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,可以有不一樣的命運\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}can have a different fate.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.17,0:25:55.31,Default,,0,0,0,,天狼星 夜空中最亮那顆星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Sirius, the brightest star in the night sky,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.34,0:25:58.41,Default,,0,0,0,,有一個非常暗淡的伴隨者\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}has a very faint stellar companion--
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.44,0:25:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,一顆白矮星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a white dwarf.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.85,0:26:01.75,Default,,0,0,0,,曾經像太陽一樣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It was once a Sun-like star.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.78,0:26:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,有一天 天狼星耗盡了燃料\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Someday, when Sirius runs out of fuel
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.58,0:26:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,變成了紅巨星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and becomes a red giant,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.42,0:26:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,它的物質會流向白矮星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}it will shed its substance onto the white dwarf.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.26,0:26:13.69,Default,,0,0,0,,這位伴隨者的強大引力會吸引氣體\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The intense gravity of the companion will attract that gas,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.99,0:26:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,使它們形成一個螺旋狀的圓盤\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}pulling it into a spiraling disk.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.43,0:26:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,從較大恆星出來的氣體\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When the gas from the larger star
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.60,0:26:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,落在白矮星的表面\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}falls onto the surface of the white dwarf,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.60,0:26:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,引發核爆炸\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}it will trigger nuclear explosions.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.31,0:26:29.17,Default,,0,0,0,,最大規模的爆炸會釋放\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The greatest burst will release
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.21,0:26:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,超過太陽10萬倍的能量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}100,000 times more energy than the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.71,0:26:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,每一次的爆炸被稱為 新星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Each one of those star bursts is called a "nova,"
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.71,0:26:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fn方正黑体简体\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}Nova：新星
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.82,0:26:40.02,Default,,0,0,0,,在拉丁語中就是 新 的意思\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}from the Latin for "new."
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.05,0:26:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,一顆質量相當於15個太陽的恆星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A star about 15 times as massive as the Sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.99,0:26:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,比如參宿七 一顆藍超巨星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}one like Rigel, the blue supergiant
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.96,0:26:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,獵戶座的右腳\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that forms the right foot of Orion,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.06,0:26:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,就有著不同的命運\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}has a different fate in store.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.90,0:26:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,電子的壓力不會使它的坍縮停止\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Its collapse will not be stopped by the pressure of electrons.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.64,0:26:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,它持續坍縮\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The star will keep falling in on itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.87,0:27:01.87,Default,,0,0,0,,直到原子核過度擁擠\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}until its nuclei become so overcrowded
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.91,0:27:04.34,Default,,0,0,0,,開始相互排斥\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that they push back.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.65,0:27:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,參宿七會縮小差不多10萬倍\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Rigel will shrink down about 100,000 times,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.72,0:27:13.02,Default,,0,0,0,,直到原子核之間沒有距離\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}until there's no space left between the nuclei
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.05,0:27:15.25,Default,,0,0,0,,無法再縮小\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and it can shrink no more.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.03,0:27:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,到那時 它引發\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}At that point, it ignites
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.49,0:27:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,一場更強烈的核反應 超新星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a more powerful nuclear reaction, a supernova.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.87,0:27:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,大部分的恆星演變\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Most stellar evolution
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.44,0:27:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,要經歷幾百萬或者幾十億年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}takes millions or billions of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.54,0:27:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,但是內部的坍縮\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But the interior collapse
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.28,0:27:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,引發超新星爆炸只需要幾秒鐘\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that triggers a supernova explosion takes only seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.18,0:27:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,只剩下一個原子核\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What remains will be an atomic nucleus
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.68,0:27:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,一個小城市那麼大\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the size of a small city--
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.39,0:27:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,急速旋轉的中子星被稱為 脈衝星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a rapidly rotating neutron star called a pulsar.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.90,0:28:05.37,Default,,0,0,0,,但對於質量超過太陽30倍的恆星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But for a star more than 30 times as massive as the Sun--
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.41,0:28:08.37,Default,,0,0,0,,比如參宿二 在獵戶座的腰帶上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a star like Alnilam, in Orion's Belt--
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.41,0:28:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,沒什麼可以阻止它的坍縮\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}there will be no stopping its collapse.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.38,0:28:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,幾百萬年後\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In a few million years,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.11,0:28:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,參宿二燃燒殆盡\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}when Alnilam runs out of fuel,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.91,0:28:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,它也會變成超新星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}it, too, will go supernova.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.95,0:28:20.29,Default,,0,0,0,,崩潰的參宿二核心\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The imploding core of Alnilam
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.32,0:28:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,質量大得 即使核力也不足以承受它的坍縮\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}will be so massive that not even nuclear forces
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.82,0:28:26.79,Default,,0,0,0,,質量大得 即使核力也不足以承受它的坍縮\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}will be strong enough to hold off its collapse.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.83,0:28:29.70,Default,,0,0,0,,沒有什麼可以抵抗這種引力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Nothing can withstand such gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.73,0:28:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,密度如此驚人的恆星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And such a star has an astonishing destiny.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.80,0:28:38.77,Default,,0,0,0,,它會持續坍縮\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It will continues to collapse,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.81,0:28:41.37,Default,,0,0,0,,超越時空的界限\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}crossing a boundary in space-time
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.41,0:28:43.58,Default,,0,0,0,,稱為 視界\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}called the "event horizon,"
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.41,0:28:43.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fn方正黑体简体\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}即黑洞表面
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.61,0:28:45.64,Default,,0,0,0,,我們無法看到內部\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}beyond which we cannot see.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.68,0:28:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,當它貫穿那個界限\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When it traverses that frontier,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.78,0:28:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,星星從我們的視線 消失得無影無蹤\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the star will vanish completely from sight.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.92,0:28:55.55,Default,,0,0,0,,它在黑洞內\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It will be inside a black hole,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.59,0:29:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,那裏的引力無比強大 即使光也無法逃脫\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a place where gravity is so strong that nothing, not even light, can escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.99,0:29:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,還有一種罕見的恆星有著更戲劇化的命運\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But there's an even more dramatic fate that awaits a rare kind of star
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.56,0:29:13.70,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的銀河系就有一顆\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There's one of them in our galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.73,0:29:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,它很不穩定 當它爆炸時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's so unstable that when it goes,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.27,0:29:19.70,Default,,0,0,0,,它不會變成新星或者超新星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}it won't become a mere nova or supernova.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.74,0:29:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,它變成更大的災難\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It'll become something far more catastrophic...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.27,0:29:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,極超新星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a hypernova.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.58,0:29:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,在我們這輩子就可能發生\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And it could happen in our lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.36,0:29:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,澳洲內陸是地球上最好的星空觀測地點之一\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There are few places on Earth to get a better view of the night sky than the Australian Outback.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.07,0:29:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,沒有建築物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}No buildings,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.43,0:29:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,沒車 沒路燈 什麼都沒有\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}no cars, streetlights, nothing out here;
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.37,0:29:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,只有星光\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}just lots of starlight...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.24,0:29:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,偶爾有幾隻袋鼠\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and the occasional kangaroo.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.61,0:29:59.08,Default,,0,0,0,,在這裏 你可以非常好的觀察銀河系\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}You can get a particularly good view of the Milky Way from down here.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.11,0:30:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,銀河的中心\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The center of our galaxy
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.81,0:30:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,高懸在空中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}rises high in the sky,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.45,0:30:04.45,Default,,0,0,0,,拱形穿過天空\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and it arches across the heavens
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.48,0:30:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,就像黑夜的脊樑\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}like the backbone of night.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.15,0:30:08.89,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的銀河系是個螺旋星雲\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We live in a spiral galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.92,0:30:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,我們看向銀河時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And when we look at the Milky Way,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.92,0:30:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,我們可以看到螺旋圓盤中幾十億顆恆星發出的光\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}we're seeing light from billions of stars in its spiral disk.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.89,0:30:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,在這樣美麗的夜空下\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And under this beautiful dark sky,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.33,0:30:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,你能看到銀河並不是一片明亮\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}you can see that the Milky Way isn't a uniform band of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.97,0:30:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,有些黑色的斑塊遮掩了星光\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There are dark patches, breaks in the starlight.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.10,0:30:27.97,Default,,0,0,0,,那些黑色的斑塊就是星際塵埃\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Those dark patches are caused by interstellar dust.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.01,0:30:31.61,Default,,0,0,0,,數量眾多的塵埃阻擋了星光\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The dust blocks the starlight, and there's lots of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.35,0:30:37.15,Default,,0,0,0,,大部分的文明中 將星星相連\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Most cultures looked up at the stars and connected the dots
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.18,0:30:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,在夜空中組成熟悉的圖案\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to form familiar images in the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.35,0:30:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,星座\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Constellations.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.63,0:30:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,但是澳洲土著\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But the Aboriginal people of Australia
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.00,0:30:51.13,Default,,0,0,0,,注意到了黑影的形狀\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}saw a pattern in the darkness
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.16,0:30:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,貫穿銀河\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}running through the Milky Way.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.27,0:30:58.27,Default,,0,0,0,,看上去像鴯鹋 一種大鳥 一種澳洲大陸本土動物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They saw an emu, a large bird native to this continent.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.30,0:31:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,它並不是由星星組成 而是在沒有星星的地方悄然出現\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Not in the stars,but in the absence of stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.38,0:31:08.11,Default,,0,0,0,,有不用的方式來看星空\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There are so many ways to look at the night sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.15,0:31:11.15,Default,,0,0,0,,上百萬年的時間裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}For a million years or more, we've watched the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.18,0:31:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,發生了很多事\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And a lot's happened in that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.89,0:31:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的銀河系中超新星爆炸大約100年一次\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Supernova explode in our galaxy about once a century.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.79,0:31:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,如果我們把所有遙望星空的夜晚壓縮成一分鐘\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If we could compress all those nights of stargazing into a single minute
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.66,0:31:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,這是我們可以看到的景象\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}this is what we would see.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.24,0:31:31.37,Default,,0,0,0,,如果把我們的眼睛比做望遠鏡\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Now, if our eyes were telescopes,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.40,0:31:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,口徑和車輪一樣大\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}if they were light buckets as big as wagon wheels
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.14,0:31:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,我們又可以識別不僅僅一種光時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and our vision was not limited to just one kind of light,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.81,0:31:42.21,Default,,0,0,0,,我們看到的銀河系就是這樣的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}then this is the Milky Way we would see.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.25,0:31:44.95,Default,,0,0,0,,近紅外光中的星系\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A galaxy in near-infrared light
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.98,0:31:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,觸手般四處蔓延的塵埃\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}with streaming tendrils of dust
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.15,0:31:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,被爆炸的超新星猛烈地甩出\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}hurled outward by those exploding supernovas,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.86,0:31:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,在無數星星的映襯下顯現出來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}silhouetted against a backdrop of countless stars
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.69,0:31:57.63,Default,,0,0,0,,大約7500光年以外\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}About 7,500 light-years away,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.66,0:31:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,銀河系的另一端\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in another part of our galaxy,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.90,0:32:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,有一場巨變\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}there is a place of upheaval
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.07,0:32:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,規模大得難以想像\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}on an inconceivable scale.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.68,0:32:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,這是船底座星雲\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This is the Carina Nebula.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.85,0:32:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,一台恆星製造機\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A star-making machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.06,0:32:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,光線要用50年的時間才能貫穿\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It takes a ray of light 50 years to cross it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.07,0:32:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,巨大的恆星在這裏誕生\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The titanic stars born here
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.44,0:32:37.71,Default,,0,0,0,,強烈的紫外線輻射烤焦了周圍的氣體和塵埃\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}sear the surrounding gas and dust with their fierce ultraviolet radiation.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.74,0:32:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,巨大的恆星死亡時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When a massive star dies,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.21,0:32:43.45,Default,,0,0,0,,將它自己炸成碎片\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}it blows itself to smithereens.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.12,0:32:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,它的物質被推得四處紛飛\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Its substance is propelled across the vastness
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.85,0:32:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,被星光攪動\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to be stirred by starlight
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.89,0:32:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,被引力匯聚\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and gathered up by gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.19,0:32:55.02,Default,,0,0,0,,由恆星變成塵埃\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Stars to dust
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.06,0:32:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,再由塵埃變為恆星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and dust to stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.90,0:33:00.76,Default,,0,0,0,,宇宙中 沒有廢物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In the cosmos, nothing is wasted.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.90,0:33:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,但是恆星的質量有一個上限\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But there's an upper limit to how massive a star can be.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.14,0:33:11.54,Default,,0,0,0,,17世紀時 愛德蒙·哈雷\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Back in the 17th century, when Edmond Halley
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.58,0:33:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,跨過赤道 繪製南方的星座圖\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}crossed the equator to map the southern constellations,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.28,0:33:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,海山二看上去只是一顆暗星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Eta Carinae seemed like just another faint star.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.28,0:33:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fn方正黑体简体\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}一個位於船底星座
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.55,0:33:20.35,Default,,0,0,0,,但到了1843年 海山二\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But in 1843, Eta Carinae
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.38,0:33:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,突然變成了天空中第二亮的星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}suddenly became the second brightest star in the sky,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.12,0:33:25.79,Default,,0,0,0,,只是比天狼星稍暗\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}outshined only by Sirius.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.82,0:33:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,從此開始爆發\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And it's been flipping out ever since.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.46,0:33:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,那個啞鈴形的雲團\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That dumbbell-shaped cloud
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.67,0:33:36.87,Default,,0,0,0,,就是爆發的膨脹殘餘\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is the expanding remnant of that event.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.41,0:33:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,中心是一顆瘋狂的恆星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}At its center is one crazy star.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.51,0:33:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,說到不穩定\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Talk about unstable
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.41,0:33:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,海山二比太陽的質量大出至少100倍\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Eta Carinae is at least 100 times more massive than the Sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.02,0:33:53.29,Default,,0,0,0,,並且發出比太陽多500萬倍的光\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and pouring out five million times more light.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.32,0:33:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,它一直在挑戰恆星質量的上限\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's pushing the upper limit of what a star can be.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.83,0:34:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,還有 有證據顯示 海山二\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What's more, there's evidence that Eta Carinae
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.66,0:34:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,飽受它那邪惡兄弟的重力折磨\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is being gravitationally tormented by an evil twin--
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.43,0:34:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,那是一顆繞它運行的恆星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}another massive star in orbit around it
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.50,0:34:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,之間的距離就像土星到太陽的距離\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}as close as Saturn is to the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.41,0:34:16.34,Default,,0,0,0,,超級巨大的恆星內核發出大量的光\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The core of a supermassive star pours out so much light
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.38,0:34:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,以致向外的壓力蓋過了恆星的引力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that the outward pressure can overwhelm the star's gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.91,0:34:22.35,Default,,0,0,0,,如果恆星過於巨大\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If a star is too massive,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.38,0:34:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,它的輻射壓力超過它的引力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}its radiation pressure overpowers its gravity
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.05,0:34:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,就會將這顆星炸裂\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and blows the star apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.69,0:34:31.66,Default,,0,0,0,,海山二的命運\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The fate of Eta Carinae was sealed
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.69,0:34:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,在幾百萬年前誕生時就已經注定\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}when it was born millions of years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.13,0:34:36.20,Default,,0,0,0,,當它最終爆炸時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When it finally does blow up
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.23,0:34:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,說不定 已經爆炸了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and who knows, maybe it already has;
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.57,0:34:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,畢竟 我們看到的光\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}after all, we're looking at it by light that left the star
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.30,0:34:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,是7500年前發出的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}7,500 years ago--
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.80,0:34:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,那會是我們從沒見過的大災難\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}it will be a cataclysm unlike anything we've seen before.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.77,0:34:49.71,Default,,0,0,0,,極超新星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A hypernova.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.66,0:35:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,爆炸威力大得使超新星看上去就如同鞭炮一樣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}An explosion so powerful, it'll make a supernova seem like a firecracker by comparison.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.56,0:35:09.73,Default,,0,0,0,,如果附近有太陽系\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If there are nearby solar systems
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.76,0:35:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,伴隨有生命的行星 它們的死期到了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}with planets harboring life, their days are numbered.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.10,0:35:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,極超新星噴出大量的輻射\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A hypernova spews so much radiation into space--
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.44,0:35:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,不只光 還有X射線 伽馬射線\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}not just light, but X-rays and gamma rays--
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.74,0:35:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,幾十光年外的行星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that planets that are dozens
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.78,0:35:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,或者甚至幾百光年外的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}or perhaps hundreds of light-years away
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.15,0:35:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,都會喪失它們的大氣層\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}could be stripped of their atmospheres
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.11,0:35:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,然後被死亡輻射籠罩\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and bathed in deadly radiation.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.78,0:35:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,它可以肆虐周圍幾千個恆星系統\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It would wreak havoc in thousands of nearby star systems.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.02,0:35:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,現在 你可能好奇\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Right about now, you're probably asking yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.69,0:35:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,我們安全嗎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}"Are we safe?"
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.13,0:35:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,如果海山二爆炸\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If Eta Carinae blows up,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.49,0:35:44.13,Default,,0,0,0,,地球怎麼辦\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}what happens to Earth?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.16,0:35:47.33,Default,,0,0,0,,放心吧 地球不會有事\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Rest assured, Earth will be just fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.37,0:35:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,記住 我們離它7500光年呢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Remember, we're 7,500 light-years away from Eta Carinae.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.47,0:35:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,恆星放出的輻射強度\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The intensity of radiation from a star,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.61,0:35:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,即使是一顆爆炸的恆星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}even an exploding star,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.48,0:35:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,隨著距離急劇下降\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}falls off rapidly with distance.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.71,0:36:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,即使這樣 海山二的謝幕演出\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But still, Eta Carinae in its death throes
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.15,0:36:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,依然會非常精彩\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}will put on quite a show.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.15,0:36:05.62,Default,,0,0,0,,它會點亮南半球的夜空\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It will light up the night of the southern hemisphere
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.65,0:36:07.99,Default,,0,0,0,,亮得如同月亮一樣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}with the brightness of a second moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.02,0:36:12.29,Default,,0,0,0,,奉獻上最激動人心的告別演出\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The most dramatic swan song a star can sing.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.63,0:36:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的祖先崇拜太陽\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Our ancestors worshipped the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.33,0:36:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,他們絕不是愚蠢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And they were far from foolish.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.40,0:36:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,對太陽和恆星的崇拜很有道理\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It makes good sense to revere the Sun and stars,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.14,0:36:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,因為我們是它們的孩子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}because we are their children.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.54,0:36:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,岩石中的硅 空氣中的氧\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The silicon in the rocks, the oxygen in the air,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.01,0:36:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,DNA中的碳 摩天大樓中的鐵\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the carbon in our DNA, the iron in our skyscrapers,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.88,0:36:39.15,Default,,0,0,0,,珠寶中的銀\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the silver in our jewelry
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.19,0:36:42.99,Default,,0,0,0,,都是恆星們幾十億年前創造的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}were all made in stars billions of years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.02,0:36:46.69,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的星球 我們的社會 還有我們自己\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Our planet, our society and we ourselves
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.73,0:36:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,都是星塵\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}are stardust.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.76,0:36:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,是什麼使原子們這麼活躍\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Well, what is it that makes the atoms dance?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.93,0:36:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,恆星的能量是如何轉變為\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}How is the energy of a star transformed
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.70,0:36:59.71,Default,,0,0,0,,世界上所發生的一切呢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}into everything that happens in the world?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.74,0:37:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,什麼是能量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What is energy?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.01,0:37:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,我們都身處其中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We're awash in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.71,0:37:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,當氫原子在太陽中聚合\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When hydrogen atoms fuse inside the Sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.51,0:37:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,產生氦原子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}they make helium atoms.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.22,0:37:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,這種核聚變發出一股能量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And this fusion emits a burst of energy
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.72,0:37:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,可以在太陽內部遊蕩1千萬年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that can wander inside the Sun for ten million years
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.02,0:37:16.49,Default,,0,0,0,,然後到達表面\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}before making its way to the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.52,0:37:19.02,Default,,0,0,0,,然後獲得自由\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And once there, it's free to fly
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.06,0:37:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,直接向地球飛來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}straight from the Sun to the Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.26,0:37:23.90,Default,,0,0,0,,就是可見光\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}as visible light.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.93,0:37:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,如果它撞擊在葉子的表面\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If it should strike the surface of a leaf,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.10,0:37:30.04,Default,,0,0,0,,它就被作為化學能量保存在了地球\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}it will be stored in the plant as chemical energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.07,0:37:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,日光\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Sunshine...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.11,0:37:33.97,Default,,0,0,0,,變成月光\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}into moonshine.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.11,0:37:33.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fn方正黑体简体\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}這裏指的是一種威士忌
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.39,0:37:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,我能感受到我的大腦把葡萄酒的化學能量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I can feel my brain turning the chemical energy of the wine
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.13,0:37:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,轉變為思想的電能\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}into the electrical energy of my thoughts
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.30,0:38:01.03,Default,,0,0,0,,指揮我的聲帶\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and directing my vocal chords
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.07,0:38:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,產生我說話的聲能\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to produce the acoustic energy of my voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.84,0:38:06.27,Default,,0,0,0,,這種能量的轉換\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Such transformations of energy
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.31,0:38:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,無時無刻都在發生\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}are happening everywhere all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.91,0:38:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,太陽的能量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Energy from our star
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.58,0:38:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,驅動風和浪\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}drives the wind and the waves
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.61,0:38:14.41,Default,,0,0,0,,還有我們四周的生命\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and the life around us.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.45,0:38:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,有這樣大量的清潔能源是多麼幸運的事情\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}How lucky we are to have this vast source of clean energy
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.92,0:38:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,這簡直是給所有人的天賜之物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}falling like manna from heaven on all of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.86,0:38:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,敬 安妮·坎農\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}To Annie Jump Cannon,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.79,0:38:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,亨麗愛塔·勒維特\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Henrietta Swan Leavitt
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.46,0:38:27.09,Default,,0,0,0,,還有塞西莉亞·佩恩\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and Cecilia Payne
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.13,0:38:30.06,Default,,0,0,0,,感謝她們開創了現代天文物理學\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for blazing the trail to modern astrophysics.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.10,0:38:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,還要敬 太陽的所有姐妹們\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And to all the sisters of the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.94,0:38:43.91,Default,,0,0,0,,宇宙中一切都逃不過改變\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There's no refuge from change in the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.94,0:38:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,從現在以後的壹千萬或兩千萬年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Some ten or 20 million years from now,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.81,0:38:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,在宇宙中只是片刻\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}it'll seem for a cosmic moment
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.12,0:38:52.82,Default,,0,0,0,,彷彿獵戶俄裏翁終於要抓到七姐妹了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}as if Orion is finally about to catch the seven sisters.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.85,0:38:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,但在他抓住她們之前\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But before he has them in his clutches,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.46,0:38:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,獵戶座最大的幾顆恆星就會變成超新星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the biggest stars of Orion will go supernova.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.16,0:39:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,獵戶座對昂宿星座的追趕會從此停止\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Orion's pursuit of the Pleiades will finally end,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.30,0:39:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,那七位姐妹\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and the seven sisters
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.80,0:39:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,會緩緩地投入銀河系的臂彎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}will glide serenely into the waiting arms of the Milky Way
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.71,0:39:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,我們在地球上對太陽升起發出贊嘆\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We on Earth marvel and rightly so-- at the return of our solitary Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.34,0:39:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,在遙遠的球狀星雲中 從一個環繞恆星的行星上看\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But from a planet orbiting a star in a distant globular cluster,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.72,0:39:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,還能看到更多驚艷的黎明\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a still more glorious dawn awaits.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.09,0:39:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,不是太陽升起\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Not a sunrise...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.26,0:39:31.19,Default,,0,0,0,,而是星系的升起\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but a galaxy rise.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.22,0:39:35.29,Default,,0,0,0,,2千億顆太陽照耀的早晨\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A morning filled with 200 billion suns.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.33,0:39:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,銀河系的升起\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The rising of the Milky Way.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.33,0:39:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,巨大的螺旋狀伴隨者坍塌的氣體雲團\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}An enormous spiral form with collapsing gas clouds,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.07,0:39:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,凝結的行星系統 發光的超巨星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}condensing planetary systems, luminous supergiants,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.74,0:39:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,穩定的中年太陽，紅巨星，白矮星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}stable middle-aged suns, red giants, white dwarfs,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.68,0:39:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,行星狀星雲 超新星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}planetary nebulas, supernovas,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.11,0:39:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,中子星 脈衝星 黑洞\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}neutron stars, pulsars, black holes
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.08,0:39:57.58,Default,,0,0,0,,有充分的理由認為\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and, there is every reason to think,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.62,0:40:01.89,Default,,0,0,0,,還有其他的天體 我們尚未發現\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}other exotic objects that we have yet to discover.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.92,0:40:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,從這樣的一個世界 高懸於銀河系\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}From such a world, high above the Milky Way,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.79,0:40:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,這麼的清晰 清晰地如同我們世界起源時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}it would be clear, as it is beginning to be clear on our world,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.70,0:40:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,我們由原子和眾星組成\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that we are made by the atoms and the stars,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.04,0:40:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的物質 我們的形態\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that our matter and our form
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.10,0:40:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,由偉大而古老的宇宙鍛造\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}are forged by the great and ancient cosmos,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.74,0:40:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,我們也是這個宇宙的一部分\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of which we are a part.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.83,0:40:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,中文翻譯：@SaltyEggPain timhal
